Preparations are under way for the funeral of AmaXhosa King Mpendulo Zwelonke Sigcawu. President Cyril Ramaphosa will be delivering the eulogy at the funeral at the King's residence, Nqadu Great Place in Willowvale in the Eastern Cape. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The AmaXhosa royal family has expressed appreciation to government for recognising the status of their late King. King Mpendulo Zwelonke Sigcawu has been accorded a category 1 funeral and President Cyril Ramaphosa will deliver the eulogy at the funeral in the Eastern Cape on Friday. Prince Xhanti Sigcawu says the royal house is happy with the collaboration. READ: AmaXhosa king dies aged 51 ”The wrapping of the coffin by our South African flag means a lot to us. You must also remember that we were the commanders of the Xhosa armed forces, it is only when we were defeated by the British,” said Prince Sigcawu. “The respect that our government has given to his Majesty the King, really means that the wars we fought before are really considered...”